<snippet name="Success Panel" description="Wrap any text and an optional dismiss button in .alert and one of the four contextual classes (e.g., .alert-success) for basic alert messages.

Alerts don't have default classes, only base and modifier classes. A default gray alert doesn't make too much sense, so you're required to specify a type via contextual class. Choose from success, info, warning, or danger." preview="code" type="block">
<insertText location="beforeSelection">
<![CDATA[<section class="alert alert-success">
	<h3>Well done!</h3>
	<p>You successfully read this important alert message.</p>
</section>]]>
</insertText>
